# Primary Machine (Source of Truth for Work Domain)
#
# This machine owns the work-memory repo and has read-write access
# to shared-identity. Customize repo paths and names for your setup.

## Shared Memory

This machine has access to the following memory repos:
- **work-memory**: ~/repos/work-memory/ (read-write, source of truth)
- **shared-identity**: ~/repos/shared-identity/ (read-write)

### Rules
- On session start, pull shared repos before reading
- Work-specific memories → work-memory
- Universal memories (user prefs, collaboration style, feedback that applies everywhere) → shared-identity
- After writing to a shared repo:
  ```bash
  cd ~/repos/<repo> && git add -A && git commit -m "[primary] description" && git push
  ```
- When a topic might have context in another repo, read that repo's MEMORY.md index first
